main event: A round, blue-white object the size of a baseball was observed for one and a half hours over Kadoka, South Dakota on November 26, 1956.
interesting points: The object appeared at an altitude of 1,000 feet and moved in a northeasterly direction at 300 knots, rising in elevation and fading from sight.
The object could not be resolved visually or through binoculars.
The report states the object was likely a balloon, possibly an aircraft, or of unknown origin.
Additional analysis and results were to be included in a monthly UFO summary report.
The report includes details from military and civilian observers, as well as radar data.
sighted object: a round, blue-white object the size of a baseball
